}{}\begin{equation*} P_i^t (j,k_{\rm s} ) = \sigma _i (t,j,k_{\rm s} ) = \frac{1}{{\Gamma (j)}}\int_0^{jk_{\rm s} t} {x^{j - 1} e^{ - x} dx} \end{equation*}\end{document}For a single-step reaction (j = 1), this simplifies to the exponential distribution:
